         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Stanley ¶  23rd Sept 1875, ¶ Baron Von Mueller Gov Botanist ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honour to acknowledge receipt of your kind reply to my previous note respecting the seed of the Tramoso. ¶  ¶ The seed...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.09.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Augustine</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 168.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">M has written on the back of the letter</seg>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">:</seg> Can Dr Hooker kindly inform me, what this plant is, and if of value procure the seeds. F. V. M.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotations by Joseph Hooker</seg>(?)<seg style="font-style: italic; "> on front page in pencil</seg>: DO <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and in ink</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>An. (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">letter not found</seg>); <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and on the back of the sheet in ink by Joseph Hooker(?):</seg> Tremoço | = Lupinus albus. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">In another hand in ink</seg>: Written to Gr[…].</p>
               </note>Stanley<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Near Beechworth, Vic.</p>
               </note> 23rd Sept 1875,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller Gov Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honour to acknowledge receipt of your kind reply to my previous note respecting the seed of the Tramoso.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The seeds of this plant would be easily procurable at St Michael's, in the Western Islands,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>São Miguel, Azores?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and would be at once recognisable by the name Tramoso, and I have no doubt they would be gladly procured by the British Consul there at your request.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall, very probably, be in Melbourne during the coming Summer, and I shall do myself the honour of waiting upon and explain more fully the use of the plant, mode of cultivation &amp;c.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">M's account of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lupinus albus</seg> in B76.13.03, p. 121, includes: 'It is famed as the "Tramoso" in Portugal, to suppress sorrel and other obstinate weeds by its close and easy growth. The lentil-like seeds … through boiling or soaking in salt water, become edible'. Similar passages occur in later editions of the work, e.g., B85.13.26, p. 204.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honour to be Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Joseph Augustine</p>
         </div>
      </body>
